                    {
                        "A":  "ID803 - Vega"
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  "List of Safety Mechanism"
                    },
                    {
                        "C":  "SM#",
                        "D":  "Development specification request No.",
                        "E":  "Addressed Part",
                        "F":  "Safety Mechanism / Measure",
                        "G":  "IC Detection Method or \r\nRequired Failsafe Solution",
                        "H":  "Software (external MCU) Proposed Detection Method or \r\nRequired Failsafe Solution",
                        "I":  "IC Mitigation Action\r\n(action after detection)",
                        "J":  "Argument",
                        "K":  "ISO 26262-5\r\nAnnex D",
                        "L":  "Diagnostic Coverage",
                        "M":  "Comments"
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  1,
                        "C":  "SM01",
                        "D":  "SR#83",
                        "E":  "REF, LDO",
                        "F":  "Comparator: VDD Under-voltage",
                        "G":  "Vega monitors system supply VDD pin voltage. If the supply voltage falls below a predefined threshold, the device transitions to OFF state, and all switches are set to open.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega resets internal logic and sets all switches to open.\r\nMCU re-inits switches after undervoltage",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  2,
                        "C":  "SM02",
                        "D":  "SR#81",
                        "E":  "REF, LDO",
                        "F":  "Comparator: VDD Over-voltage",
                        "G":  "If VDD voltage exceeds the max nominal voltage, the switch between CPN and VDD is opened and the fault bit, VDD_OV_FLT, is set to 1.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega sets the switch between CPN and VDD to open.\r\nMCU re-inits switches after undervoltage",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  3,
                        "C":  "SM03",
                        "D":  "SR#92",
                        "E":  "SW_BANK, LOGIC",
                        "F":  "Comparator: Resistive FET Detection",
                        "G":  "Resistive FET, when it is supposed to be short. If the voltage across the switch when it is shorted is more than the predefined threshold, all the corresponding bits in the FLT_LEDON are set in the volatile memory.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  4,
                        "C":  "SM04",
                        "D":  "SR#16",
                        "E":  "SW_BANK, LOGIC",
                        "F":  "Comparator: LED Open Detection",
                        "G":  "Vega monitors open condition across each SW FET. If the voltage across each switch exceeds predefined threshold, the switch FET is closed and all the corresponding bits in the FLT_LEDON are set in the volatile memory.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  5,
                        "C":  "SM05",
                        "D":  "SR#20",
                        "E":  "SW_BANK, LOGIC",
                        "F":  "Comparator: LED Short Detection",
                        "G":  "Vega monitors short condition across each SW FET and reports if the voltage across each switch decreases below the predefined threshold during the time that switch is supposed to be open, a corresponding register bit is set in the volatile memory. LED short condition is reported to MCU via UART.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  6,
                        "C":  "SM06",
                        "D":  "SR#28, 29",
                        "E":  "SW_BANK, LOGIC",
                        "F":  "Driver Health Check",
                        "G":  "To check the health of the SW FET driver, the DRV_CHK bit in the OUTCTRL register can be set by MCU. Upon setting this bit, all the gate driver outputs are disconnected from the output switches and the gate biases are pulled low. If all the switches are correctly turned off and are at high-z, all the corresponding bits in the FAULT_OPEN_OR_DRV are set to \"1\".",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D2.3.2, self-test supported by hardware",
                        "L":  0.9
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  8,
                        "C":  "SM08",
                        "D":  "SR#33",
                        "E":  "CS, ADC",
                        "F":  "ADC: LED Current Monitoring",
                        "G":  "If the CSEN bit is set in the SYSCFG register, the voltage across CS pin and GND is measured using an ADC. The measured results are stored in the CS register in the volatile memory.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D.2.4.4, monitoring outputs derated due to ADC sampling",
                        "L":  0.9
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  9,
                        "C":  "SM09",
                        "D":  "SR#123",
                        "E":  "LOGIC",
                        "F":  "UART Communication Watchdog",
                        "G":  "If CMWEN bit in SYSCFG register is set, a CRC error check is performed on each UART transaction received from the MCU. If a valid UART transaction for more than a pre-programmed time is not received, the device enters the FAIL-SAFE state, and an associated error bit is set in the status register.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D2.5.6, D2.5.7, D2.5.8",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  10,
                        "C":  "SM10",
                        "D":  "SR#109",
                        "E":  "LOGIC",
                        "F":  "Internal UART Watchdog Check",
                        "G":  "A health check of the UART watchdog is performed upon power up.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega enters DIA2 state mode.\r\nMCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D2.5.8",
                        "L":  0.9
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  11,
                        "C":  "SM11",
                        "E":  "OSC",
                        "F":  "Internal Clock Watchdog Check",
                        "G":  "When ID803 operates with the internal clock, a clock watchdog monitors the clock. If the internal clock fails, a sys_reset to the digital is issued and all switches are set to open position. In this case PWR bit is set.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega sets the corresponding switch open.\r\nMCU re-inits switches",
                        "K":  "D2.7.3",
                        "L":  0.6
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  12,
                        "C":  "SM12",
                        "E":  "SW_BANK, LOGIC",
                        "F":  "PWM Monitoring",
                        "G":  "The diagnostic PWM counter checks the output of each channel PWM counter in a round robin to make sure the output of each PWM counter is as programmed. If a PWM error count occurs, PWM_ERR bit is set in the STATUS register and a bit for a corresponding PWM counter is set in the PWM_MISCOUNT registers.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D2.7.2",
                        "L":  0.9
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  13,
                        "C":  "SM13",
                        "D":  "SR#74",
                        "E":  "SW_BANK, LOGIC",
                        "F":  "Comparator: FS Pin State",
                        "G":  "During FAIL-SAFE state, switches are set according to the FS-pin voltage, all switches shall be set to open if the voltage on the FS-pin is lower than VIL-TH, and shall be set to close if the voItage on the FS-pin is more than VIH-TH. The FS-pin can be connected to GND or the VDD. There is a FS_PIN bit in the STATUS1 register that shows the voltage level of the FS pin.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega turn off or turn on all switches according to FS pin status.\r\nMCU re-inits switches",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  14,
                        "C":  "SM14",
                        "D":  "SR#53",
                        "E":  "CP",
                        "F":  "Comparator: CP Voltage Monitoring",
                        "G":  "The charge pump voltage is monitored. If the charge pump voltage is decreased below a threshold, all the switches are set to open position. The CHPMP_ERR bit is set in the STATUS2 register if a charge pump error occurs.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega sets the corresponding switch open.\r\nMCU re-inits switches",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  15,
                        "C":  "SM15",
                        "D":  "SR#84,85",
                        "E":  "REF, LDO",
                        "F":  "Comparator: Internal Supply Monitoring",
                        "G":  "When 1.8V internal voltage goes out of a specified voltage range, it generates a POR that resets digital and sets the output switches to open. The LDO_UV_FLT bit is then set to default value of \u00271\u0027.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "Vega sets the corresponding switch open.\r\nMCU re-inits switches",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  16,
                        "C":  "SM16",
                        "E":  "REF, ADC",
                        "F":  "ADC: SBG ADC Reading",
                        "G":  "IC features a secondary bandgap (typ. 1.2V) that\u0027s digitized using the primary bandgap\u0027s 2V reference. Results are stored in BGR register.",
                        "H":  "check registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, comparison but derated due to ADC sampling",
                        "L":  0.9
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  17,
                        "C":  "SM17",
                        "D":  "SR#99",
                        "E":  "TEMP",
                        "F":  "ADC: Thermal Limit",
                        "G":  "The PTAT  voltage generated by die temperature monitor module is measured by an ADC. The measured die temperature value is compared with 175C thermal limit in digital. The TLMT bit is set in STATUS2 register if thermal limit occurs.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "When TSDEN\u003c1:0\u003e is set to 0x00, there is no action is taken for the switches when TLIMIT is reached. When it is set to 0x03, switches are set to open when TLIMIT is reached.n and MCU resets IC.",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, comparison but derated due to ADC sampling",
                        "L":  0.9
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  18,
                        "C":  "SM18",
                        "E":  "LOGIC",
                        "F":  "ECC",
                        "G":  "The ECC will correct 1 bit error and detect 2 bit error.",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D2.5.2 withSECDED and short exposition by NVM copy",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  20,
                        "C":  "SM20",
                        "E":  "LDO",
                        "F":  "Comparator: LDO Overvoltage",
                        "G":  "check against set limits",
