                        "I":  "MCU wait for normal voltage",
                        "K":  "D.2.1.2, tight comparator",
                        "L":  0.99
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  21,
                        "C":  "SM21",
                        "E":  "LOGIC",
                        "F":  "SYNC Monitor",
                        "G":  "The bit is set when SYNC pulse high duration is within в”¬в–’6.25% of PWM register configuration, and reset if it is out of range",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
                        "I":  "MCU resets IC",
                        "K":  "D2.6.1",
                        "L":  0.6
                    },
                    {
                        "B":  22,
                        "C":  "SM22",
                        "E":  "CP, SW_BANK",
                        "F":  "Matrix SW POR",
                        "G":  "If the floating supply in the switch module falls below a defined threshold, the switch is set to open. This mechanism is  triggered if the internal supply to the regulator or the VDD supply, or the charge pump fails. ID803 sets the corresponding  switch open and all the corresponding bits in the FLT_MATRIX_POR register are set to \"1\".",
                        "H":  "check status registers for fails",
